//terminal commands
Ctrl+Pageup/doun	-> scrolling 1Page up/down
Ctrl+Home/End		-> move to home/end in the terminal

//How to get public and secure keys
(on teraterm)
1.click settings/SSH keysgen on the window.
2.touch "Generation"
3.write your password in passphrase of keys.
4.optically sign comments.
5.save a public key and a secure key.
(if filename extension dont show, public and secure keys are different names.)
6.run SSH transfer and login as a user.
7.move a public key to /home/USER/.ssh and rename it "authorized_keys"
(Permission of authorized_keys is 644)
8.disconnect SSH transfer and run teraterm.
9.login USER as public key authorization.
10.make you happy!

//vimrc
Default option "vimrc"
open vimrc "~/.vimrc"

//Copy and Paste
Copy = sentense or words to double click
Paste = right click (-disabled) or Alt + V (Ctrl-V in windows)

//force log out
1) w command
2) find your user
3) run "ps ax | grep sshd"
4) display <process ID>
5) run "kill -9 <process ID>"

//vi editor
vsplit		->	divide half vertically
Ctrl + w + h	->	move to right window
Ctrl + w + l	->	move to left window
(to execute)
vi(m) -O fileA fileB	->	open fileA and fileB vertically(O is large o, not zero)

